    "contract_note": "result_bind_inhabitant(self, T, E, U) holds iff the monadic-bind laws hold: (1) bind(Ok(v), f) = f(v) for all v : T; (2) bind(Err(e), f) = Err(e) for all e : E; (3) bind(bind(m, f), g) = bind(m, x -> bind(f(x), g)) for all m, f, g. The f slot must produce a Result<U,E>; the error type is preserved across bind. Depends on concept:result -> c (PR #668) for the underlying Ok/Err constructors.",
